            "id": "s1_story",
            "label": "The Story of Me",
            "color": "#c89048",
            "desc": "The narrative you tell yourself about who you are and how you got here. It is mostly fiction. Not because you are lying, but because memory is a reconstruction and identity is a story stitched together from the pieces that survived. The story is necessary. It is also a draft. You are allowed to revise it.",
