            "id": "s4_nostalgia",
            "label": "Nostalgia",
            "color": "#e8b860",
            "desc": "Homesickness for a time. Often a sweetened version of a time that, when it was happening, did not feel sweet. Nostalgia tells you something true about what you needed and a great deal that is false about whether you had it. It is the brain's photo filter. Politicians sell nostalgia in bulk because it scratches a real itch with a counterfeit fingernail.",
