            "label": "Collective Memory",
            "color": "#a87830",
            "desc": "What a whole society agrees to remember and what it agrees to forget. Monuments, holidays, textbooks, anniversaries — these are the visible scaffolding. The invisible part is everything edited out. A nation's collective memory is a fight, every time, over which past it intends to live with.",
