                "color": "#b87038",
                "desc": "What gets passed down. Eye color is the easy example. Most of what gets inherited is messier — predispositions, tendencies, ranges. The trait is rarely the gene. The trait is what the gene does in conversation with thousands of other genes and the world the body grew up in.",
