            "id": "f_gen_disease",
            "label": "Genetic Disease",
            "color": "#b07038",
            "desc": "The flip side of inheritance. Some genetic conditions are simple and devastating. Most are complex — a tilt in risk, not a verdict. Genetic medicine has gotten very good at testing and not nearly as good at treating. The science of identifying the problem is decades ahead of the science of fixing it.",
