                "label": "Medical Genetics",
                "color": "#c88848",
                "desc": "Engineering applied to disease. Gene therapies are starting to cure conditions that were death sentences a generation ago. Each new therapy costs in the millions. Access is rationed by insurance, geography, and luck. The miracle and the gatekeeping arrived together.",
