                "label": "Rivalry",
                "color": "#a06030",
                "desc": "The competition that nobody quite admits is happening. Sibling rivalry is older than language and as common as siblings. Most of it is benign. Some of it shapes a life — the comparison that became a wound, the favor that never got returned, the decade you spent trying to be the one who got noticed.",
